reviews.text: With excellent art throughout the year , the galleries here are always chopping and changing something new every few months. A real eclectic mix of artists; some well known, others less so, there's also piqnic on the roof for a well earned bevy.

The art was great but the accessibility of the building is horrible. I injured my knee and ankle earlier in the day and despite having a visible limp, the guards had to be asked repeatedly for the lift and only begrudgingly called for the elevator when I was going 3 and 5 floors down. For single floors I just hobbled down because they made such a big production out of it when I was going multiple floors.
Nice building. The janitors downstairs, they are a little pushy because of the crowd they get.
Very very great place to visit. And of cuz to see art and buy art.
House the majority of the quality art galleries  of Hong Kong

reviews.text:
今個weekend繼續抓住restaurant week最後最後的尾巴, 連去兩家秘魯餐廳, 哈哈
-
雖然蠻常吃藜麥但對秘魯菜完全沒概念, 不能說正不正宗 🤷🏻‍♀️ 也想去秘魯但一想到要飛30多小時就...
-
食物偏重口味香料下的很夠, 全都小碟小碟的但吃下來也很飽 (在我當時不太餓的狀態下), 烤蔬菜軟taco看起來不怎樣但口感十足, 沾滿秘製酱汁的脆嫩蔬菜配上炸地瓜絲和充滿玉米香的soft taco shell, 幾口就被我解決了！
-
燉牛面頰非常嫩也很入味, 每一口都吃到濃濃的骨膠原呀, 小驚艷的一碗~ 吃了兩道满意的菜後對甜品很有期望, 可惜, Banana flan甜的太可怕了, 除了甜味吃不到其他味道... 幸好上面的黑芝麻冰淇淋不錯 
-
精緻的菜會想再來, 不過希望他們的通風能加強. 一進去已是滿餐廳煙霧, 吃著吃著都快流汗了... 吃完後全身都是油煙味呢
-
Amazing food. Interesting flavors and so pretty too. Great space and excellent service.

Cocktails and mixed drinks at happy hour are poorly made. Promotions have fine print, better check with the staff to see what the requirements are to qualify for buy 1 get 1 Wednesdays. Not sure about the food, hopefully better than their drinks and thats not a hard feat.

Je n'ai essayé que la terrasse pour y boire un verre et manger un petit en-cas. Bonne musique, lieu agréable, plat de fruits excellent et cocktails créatifs.
Mise à jour: j'y ai mangé d'excellents ceviche ! La viande y est également exceptionnelle, par contre j'ai trouvé les tacos sans intérêt.
Bon choix de vins, personnel agréable et disponible.

Very stylish restaurant with lovely terrace bar. 
Lots of greenery and relaxed seating in the heart of the Central district.
Staff are friendly and efficient  & the daily " Happy Hour " is not to be missed. 
Well worth a visit when in HK .
